\begin_layout Enumerate
Discuss each of the following email protocols:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
SMTP (3 marks)
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
A protocol allowing users to send & forward e-mails from one mail server
 to another.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Performs the actual delivery of the e-mails.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
IMAP (3 marks)
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
A protocol to retrieve e-mail addresses from mail servers
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Contrary to POP protocol, IMAP has a centralized place to store e-mail address,
 and synchronize changes on the central mail server.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
New & old (undeleted) messages are available for retrieval.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
POP (3 marks)
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
Another protocol to retrieve e-mail addresses from mail servers
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Contrary to IMAP, POP does not have centralized place to store e-mail addresses.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Only new messages are available for retrieval.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\end_deeper
