\begin_layout Enumerate
GET
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
Retrieves data from a web server.
 Usually, the HTML file, scripts, and resources such as pictures are retrieved
 for display by the web browser.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
POST
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
Sends data to the server to create a new entity.
 Often used when uploading files or submitting a web form.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
POST is NOT idempotent, the same POST statement executed multiple times
 does not guarantee the same result will be made.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
PUT
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
Similar to POST, also sends data to the server to create a new entity.
 However, PUT is usually used to repalce an existing entity.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
PUT is idempotent, the same PUT statement executed multiple times will guarantee
 the same result.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
